Sonar is likely reporting duplicated test setup because both exception tests repeat the same WebClient mock chain.

Keep only **one exception test** for `OidcTokenService`, as in your screenshot, and remove the other similar exception test.

To reduce duplication further, move the common setup into a helper method:

```java
private void mockTokenExchangeChain() {
    when(webClient.post()).thenReturn(requestBodyUriSpec);
    when(requestBodyUriSpec.uri("token-uri"))
            .thenReturn(requestBodySpec);
    when(requestBodySpec.contentType(
            MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED))
            .thenReturn(requestBodySpec);
    when(requestBodySpec.body(any(BodyInserter.class)))
            .thenReturn(requestHeadersSpec);
    when(requestHeadersSpec.retrieve())
            .thenReturn(responseSpec);
    when(responseSpec.onStatus(any(), any()))
            .thenReturn(responseSpec);
}
```

Then your single exception test becomes:

```java
@Test
void exchangeToken_shouldThrowTechnicalException_whenWebClientFails() {
    mockTokenExchangeChain();

    when(responseSpec.bodyToMono(any(ParameterizedTypeReference.class)))
            .thenReturn(Mono.error(
                    new TechnicalException(
                            "Token exchange failed: invalid_grant")));

    assertThatThrownBy(() -> oidcTokenService.exchangeToken(
            "auth-code",
            "token-uri",
            validAppConfig(),
            authTransaction()))
            .isInstanceOf(TechnicalException.class)
            .hasMessageContaining("Token exchange failed");
}
```

Keep your success test separately, but also reuse the same helper:

```java
@Test
void exchangeToken_shouldReturnTokens_whenRequestSucceeds() {
    mockTokenExchangeChain();

    Map<String, Object> tokenResponse = Map.of(
            "access_token", "access-token",
            "id_token", "id-token"
    );

    when(responseSpec.bodyToMono(any(ParameterizedTypeReference.class)))
            .thenReturn(Mono.just(tokenResponse));

    Map<String, Object> result = oidcTokenService.exchangeToken(
            "auth-code",
            "token-uri",
            validAppConfig(),
            authTransaction());

    assertThat(result).isEqualTo(tokenResponse);
}
```

This gives Sonar one common mock setup and only one exception-flow test.
